<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb956d327-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3" identifier="/us/usc/t39/s1009"><num value="1009">§ 1009.</num><heading> Personnel not to receive fees</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">An officer or employee of the Postal Service may not receive any fee or perquisite from a patron of the Postal Service on account of the duties performed by virtue of his appointment, except as authorized by law.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb956d328-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3">(<ref href="/us/pl/91/375">Pub. L. 91–375</ref>, <date date="1970-08-12">Aug. 12, 1970</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/84/733">84 Stat. 733</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
